&gt; &gt;     &gt;
&gt; &gt;     &gt; JDepend 1.4, the freely-available Java package dependency
&gt; &gt;     &gt; analyzer,  has
&gt; &gt;     &gt; been released.  Of particular interest to JUnit users is
&gt; &gt;     &gt; the ability to
&gt; &gt;     &gt; write tests that automatically check metrics tolerances,
&gt; &gt;     &gt; existence of
&gt; &gt;     &gt; package dependency cycles, and package dependency constraints.
&gt; &gt;     &gt;
&gt; &gt;     &gt;
&gt; &gt;     &gt; New Features:
&gt; &gt;     &gt;
&gt; &gt;     &gt; - Added package dependency constraints to support writing
&gt; &gt;     &gt; tests that
&gt; &gt;     &gt; fail if any package dependency other than those declared in the
&gt; &gt;     &gt; dependency constraints are detected.  Refer to the
&gt; &gt;     &gt; documentation or the
&gt; &gt;     &gt; jdepend.framework.ConstraintTest class for complete examples.
&gt; &gt;     &gt;
&gt; &gt;     &gt;   For example, the following test case method will fail
&gt; &gt;     &gt; if the analyzed
&gt; &gt;     &gt; packages contain any dependencies other than those declared in
&gt; &gt; the
&gt; &gt;     &gt; dependency constraint:
&gt; &gt;     &gt;
&gt; &gt;     &gt;     public void testDependencyConstraint() {
&gt; &gt;     &gt;
&gt; &gt;     &gt;         JavaPackage ejb = new JavaPackage(&quot;com.xyz.ejb&quot;);
&gt; &gt;     &gt;         JavaPackage web = new JavaPackage(&quot;com.xyz.web&quot;);
&gt; &gt;     &gt;         JavaPackage util = new JavaPackage(&quot;com.xyz.util&quot;);
&gt; &gt;     &gt;
&gt; &gt;     &gt;         ejb.dependsUpon(util);
&gt; &gt;     &gt;         web.dependsUpon(util);
&gt; &gt;     &gt;
&gt; &gt;     &gt;         DependencyConstraint constraint = new
&gt; &gt;     &gt; DependencyConstraint();
&gt; &gt;     &gt;         constraint.addPackage(ejb);
&gt; &gt;     &gt;         constraint.addPackage(web);
&gt; &gt;     &gt;         constraint.addPackage(util);
&gt; &gt;     &gt;
&gt; &gt;     &gt;         _jdepend.analyze();
&gt; &gt;     &gt;
&gt; &gt;     &gt;         assert(_jdepend.dependencyMatch(constraint));
&gt; &gt;     &gt;     }
&gt; &gt;     &gt;
&gt; &gt;     &gt; - Added the jdepend.xmlui.JDepend class to generate
&gt; &gt;     &gt; package metrics,
&gt; &gt;     &gt; dependencies, and cycles in an XML format for easier
&gt; &gt;     &gt; integration with
&gt; &gt;     &gt; other tools.
&gt; &gt;     &gt;
&gt; &gt;     &gt;   Example usage:
&gt; &gt;     &gt;       java jdepend.xmlui.JDepend -file report.xml
&gt; &gt; /myproject/src
&gt; &gt;     &gt;
&gt; &gt;     &gt;
&gt; &gt;     &gt; The JDepend documentation is available at
&gt; &gt;     &gt;
&gt; &gt;     &gt;        http://www.clarkware.com/software/JDepend.html
&gt; &gt;     &gt;
&gt; &gt;     &gt; JDepend 1.4 can be downloaded directly from
&gt; &gt;     &gt;
&gt; &gt;     &gt;        http://www.clarkware.com/software/jdepend1.4.zip
&gt; &gt;     &gt;
